Summary: Exoplanet characterization is a critical component of current exoplanetary science. In particular, characterization of known exoplanetary systems enables studies of planetary structure and atmospheres, system architectures, orbital dynamics, and the refinement of exoplanet host star properties. This proposal aims to ensure that all known exoplanet host stars within the TESS Cycle 4 fields are included in the target list. The three main science goals of the observations are: (a) observations of potential transits and phase variations, (b) refined transit ephemerides enabling spectroscopic follow-up with future space-based facilities, and (c) detailed stellar properties through astroseismology modeling.
